replies.body:
i agree with the de-stressing. i can't count the number of times where i've been yelled at as a support for messing up one little thing. those bad games where you just question whether you should even be there
bot games have some of the most chill people, and while its nowhere near the feel of a real game, everyone tries to make people feel welcome. Play roles you normally don't, learn your way around a new champ. hell, pull out the random button and try to fill using whatever champ you get (support master yi for the win)
the peeps in bot games are for real the chillest people ive played with. if you talk about your cruddy game you just got out of, they help you out and support you. if you ask, they give friendly advice. i've rarely if ever left a bot game feeling useless and hopeless. the shenanigans you pull are too fun. (like surrendering as we destroy the nexus so both go pop. we lose the game, but everyone gets a laugh out of that. {{champion:201}}
